    "narrative": "Today\u2019s optimal build centers on our high-efficiency baserunners and favorable park matchups, with **Tyler Freeman** (71.80) and **Bryson Stott** (68.43) anchoring the lineup as our strongest plays. **Tyler Freeman** benefits from a potent combination of a 14% park boost and a soft matchup against Cristian Javier (4.68 xERA), and despite the minor suppression from the opposing catcher's efficiency, his projected leadoff spot provides the high-volume plate appearance floor we prioritize. **Bryson Stott** similarly benefits from an excellent 15% SP skill boost against Tyler Mahle, and he is a critical component of our strategy to maximize SB opportunities against a battery that isn't particularly elite at holding runners. We are also capitalizing on **Lawrence Butler** (65.37), who leverages a massive 13% platoon edge against Will Warren to push his efficiency well into our \"Strong\" start tier.\n\nOur most difficult benching decision involved **Gleyber Torres** (55.61), who finished just shy of the active roster threshold. While his 12% SP skill boost against Bailey Ober was attractive, his poor platoon efficiency and the lack of concrete lineup confirmation pushed the optimizer to favor the more stable, high-upside profiles of **Jonathan Aranda** and **Cal Raleigh**. We must also monitor the risks associated with our anchor, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (55.84); while his raw talent is undeniable, he faces a daunting matchup against Cole Ragans (2.52 xERA), which heavily suppresses his expected output. Additionally, **Yainer Diaz**, **Jonathan Aranda**, **Bryson Stott**, **Geraldo Perdomo**, **Masyn Winn**, **Tyler Freeman**, **Lawrence Butler**, **Matt Chapman**, **Gleyber Torres**, **Luis Arraez**, and **Jung Hoo Lee** remain subject to \"Lineup Pending\" volatility. If any of these players are shifted down in the order or scratched, we will need to pivot to the bench depth provided by **Wenceel Perez**, **Brendan Donovan**, **Jeremiah Jackson**, or **Drew Gilbert** to maintain our competitive edge in the 5x5 categories.",
